  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To support GRAIN&apos;s overall work in addressing food sovereignty and agro-ecology as central components of the global fight against industrial agriculture and climate change. GRAIN will advocate for community-based agricultural approaches as opposed to the current corporate-driven global food system in Africa, Asia, and Latin America. They will research and develop reports on the current food-land-climate crisis by focusing on issues of land grabbing, predatory water withdrawal practices, agro ecology; develop tools (such updated website) for other NGOs around the globe to access resources to fight for climate justice; and network with partner organizations in the Global South to share best practices and develop strategies to push for food sovereignty for communities around the globe</narrative>
  </description>
